@node "Cygnus X-1 Book 2" "Cygnus X-1 Book 2 from Hemispheres"
@toc "Cygnus X-1 Book 2"
@next "Cygnus X-1 Book 2"
@prev "Cygnus X-1 Book 2"
"@{b}@{i}@{fg shine}Cygnus X-1 Book 2: Hemispheres@{ub}@{ui}@{fg text}"

 -----------------------------------------------------------
         1. Prelude (4:27)
         2. Apollo: Bringer of Wisdom (4:36)
         3. Dionysus: Bringer of Love
         4. Armageddon: The Battle of Heart and Mind (2:55)
         5. Cygnus: Bringer of Balance (5:01)
         6. The Sphere: A Kind of Dream (1:02)
 -----------------------------------------------------------

 @{b}Cygnus X-1 Book 2: Hemispheres  1. Prelude@{ub}
 ------ --- ---- -  -----------  -  -------
 When our weary world was young
 The struggle of the ancients first began
 The Gods of Love and Reason
 Sought alone to rule the fate of Man

 They battled through the ages
 But still neither force would yield
 Their people were divided
 Every soul a battlefield...

 @{b}2. Apollo: Bringer of Wisdom@{ub}
 -  ------  ------- -- ------
 "I bring truth, and Understanding
 I bring Wit, and Wisdom fair
 Precious gifts beyond compare
 We can build a world of wonder
 I can make you all aware"

 "I will find you food and shelter
 Show you fire to keep you warm
 Through the endless winter storm
 You can live in grace and comfort
 In the world that you transform."

 @{i}The people were delighted
 Coming forth to claim their prize
 They ran to build their cities
 And converse among the wise

 But one day the streets fell silent
 Yet they knew not what was wrong
 The urge to build these fine things
 Seemed not to be so strong

 The wise men were consulted
 And the Bridge of Death was crossed
 In quest of Dionysus
 To find out what they had lost...@{ui}

 @{b}3. Dionysus: Bringer of Love@{ub}
 -- --------  ------- -- ----
 "I bring love to give you solace
 In the darkness of the night
 In the heart's eternal light
 You need only trust your feelings
 Only love can steer you right."

 "I bring laughter, I bring music
 I bring Joy and I bring Tears
 I will soothe your primal fears
 Throw off those chains of Reason
 And your prison disappears."

 @{i}The cities were abandoned
 And the forests echoed song
 They danced and lived as brothers
 They knew love could not be wrong

 Food and wine they had aplenty
 And they slept beneath the stars
 The people were contented
 And the Gods watched from afar

 But the winter fell upon them
 And it caught them unprepared
 Bringing wolves and cold starvation
 And the hearts of men despaired...@{ui}

 @{b}4. Armageddon: The Battle of Heart and Mind@{ub}
 -- ----------  --- ------ -- ----- --- ----
 The Universe divided
 As the Heart and Mind collided
 With our people left unguided
 For so many troubled years
 In a cloud of doubts and fears
 Our world was torn asunder
 Into hollow hemispheres

 Some fought themselves, some fought each other
 Most just followed one another
 Lost and aimless like their brothers
 For their Hearts were so unclear
 And the Truth could not appear
 Their spirits were divided
 Into blinded Hemispheres

 @{i}Some who did not fight
 Brought tales of old to light
 My "Rocinante'" sailed by night
 On her final flight

 To the heart of Cygnus' fearsome force
 We set our course
 Spiralled through that timeless space
 To this immortal place@{ui}


 @{b}5. Cygnus: Bringer of Balance@{ub}
 -- ------  ------- -- -------
 @{i}I have memory and awareness
 But I have no shape or form
 As a disembodied spirit
 I am dead and yet unborn

 I have passed into Olympus
 As was told in tales of old
 To the City of Immortals
 Marble white and purest gold

 I see the Gods in battle rage on high
 Thunderbolts across the sky
 I cannot move, I cannot hide
 I feel a silent scream begin inside@{ui}

 Then all at once the Chaos ceased
 A stillness fell, a sudden peace
 The Warriors felt my silent cry
 And stayed their struggle, mystified

 Apollo was atonished
 Dionysus thought me mad
 But they heard my story further
 And they wondered, and were sad

 Looking down from Olympus
 On a world of doubt and fear
 It's surface splintered into
 Sorry hemispheres

 They sat a while in silence
 Then they turned at last to me
 "We will call you Cygnus,
 The God of Balance you shall be."

 @{b}6. The Sphere: A Kind of Dream@{ub}
 -- ----------  - ---- -- -----
 @{b}@{i}We can walk our road together
 If our goals are all the same
 We can run alone and free
 If we pursue a different aim

 Let the truth of Love be lighted
 Let the love of Truth shine clear
 Sensibility
 Armed with sense and liberty
 With the Heart and Mind united
 In a single perfect Sphere@{ub}@{ui}
@endnode

@node "Circumstances" "Circumstances from Hemispheres"
@toc "Circumstances"
@next "Circumstances"
@prev "Circumstances"
"@{b}@{i}@{fg shine}Circumstances@{ub}@{ui}@{fg text}"


 A boy alone, so far from home
 Endless rooftops from my window
 I felt the gloom of empty rooms
 On rainy afternoons

 Sometimes, in confusion
 I felt so lost and disillusioned
 Innocence gave me confidence
 To go up against reality

   @{i}@{fg fill}All the same
   We take our chances
   Laughed at by Time
   Tricked by circumstances
   Plus ca change
   Plus c'est la meme chose
   The more that things change
   The more they stay the same@{ui}@{fg text}

 Now I've gained some understanding
 Of the only world that we see
 Things that I once dreamed of
 Have become reality

 These walls that still surround me
 Still contain the same old me
 Just one more who's searching for
 The world that ought to be
@endnode

@node "The Trees" "The Trees from Hemispheres"
@toc "The Trees"
@next "The Trees"
@prev "The Trees"
"@{b}@{i}@{fg shine}The Trees@{ub}@{ui}@{fg text}"


 There is unrest in the Forest
 There is trouble with the trees
 For the Maples want more sunlight
 And the Oaks ignore their pleas

 The trouble with the Maples
 (And they're quite convinced the're right)
 They say the Oaks are just too lofty
 And they grab up all the light
 But the Oaks can't help their feelings
 If they like the way they're made
 And they wonder why the Maples
 Can't be happy in their shade?

 There is trouble in the Forest
 And the creatures all have fled
 As the Maples scream "@{fg shine}Oppression@{fg text}"
 And the Oaks, just shake their heads

 So the Maples formed a Union
 And demanded equal rights
 "@{i}The Oaks are just too greedy@{ui}
 @{i}We will make them give us light@{ui}."
 Now there's no more Oak oppression,
 For they passed a noble law
 And the trees are all kept equal
 By @{bg shine}hatchet@{bg back}
 @{bg shine}Axe@{bg back},
 @{bg shine}And saw@{bg back}...
@endnode

