@node "About" "About"
@toc "About"
@next "About"
@prev "About"

 This Amiga Guide is about 4 years or more in the making.  I was heavily
invovled with it & many people were expecting to see it on AmiNet a long time
ago.  I'm sorry it has taken this long.  Many things have changed in my life
just as for anyone else.  I haven't edited this text in over a year but have
recently start modifying it. :D

 I plan to include some graphics as well as Sound samples.  So I intend to add a
History to this.  I've considered making it into HTML so it could be read by all
computer users but I'm pretty dedicated to the Amiga & it started out as an
Amiga ONLY project.  So I'm not sure yet, for now, Amiga Guide only.  Perhaps if
I get enough Email from this in a possitive direction I'll make an HTML
version.

 I've been a MASSIVE RUSH Fanatic for Years!  Actually, ever since 1974 which;
amazingly enough (Ahhhhh...WOW!) is when the trio started...commercially anyway.
;)  They are to ME then *BEST* Rock'N'Roll group ever!  I know the Stones, &
AC/DC & Led Zeppelin are huge, too & have a pretty loyal following & I won't
knock any of them because I like them a LOT, too, but RUSH is...the Pinical of
Music to me.  All of this & I consider them to be HUMAN being with Incrediable
Talent & not some kind of Gods.  Afterall, people ARE people...you know?


 RUSH is the only Group that has captured my Mind & Feelings in such a special
way.  As soon as I hear a Note from ANY song I KNOW it's them.  They are VERY
Unique.  I must admit, though, I'm SOOOOOoooooOOoooOoo tired of Tom Sawyer,
...I'm not going to go into a Major (Where's my) Thing about it though.  SO,
flame ME if you must... I'll reply with, "You know, they have OTHER Much BETTER
songs.  Have you Truely explored the well over 50 songs?"

 Me?  Well, I'm a HUGE fan of the Amiga... A500 (x2), A1000, A2000, A4000. I
have LONG dark brown salty hair (didn't use to have the Salt in it, hehe..) also
love collecting MAX HEADROOM stuff.  My other music interests consist of AC/DC,
Pink Floyd, Dio, The Art Of Noise, Megadeth, (Older) MetallicA (I cannot stand
Re/Load), Van Halen, & TONS of 50s, 60s, 70s, 80s & earlier 90s music.



 Okay, I think that wraps it up for now.  I'll add to this later.  See you
online. :)  RUSH Rocks, RUSH Rules!  The 3 Stooges on Stage!
@endnode

